An object suspected to be explosive device, on Thursday, exploded at Glory Land High School, Azugwu, Ebonyi Local Government Area of Ebonyi State, and chopped off the left hand of a SS2 student of the school identified as Chibuike and left other students with various degrees of injury. DAILY INDEPENDENT gathered that the incident which took place during break hour, around 11 a.m. caused serious confusion and panic within the school and its environs. Chibuike was rushed to the emergency unit of the Alex Ekwueme Federal Teaching Hospital, Abakaliki. Other students who were injured were taken to undisclosed hospitals for medical attention. The development caused serious panic such that when our Reporter visited the school at about 2:30 p.m., the entrance gate was under lock and key. But some of the students of the school who interacted with our reporter confirmed the incident, adding that Chibuike, was playing with the device when it exploded. “I was in the school when it exploded. I can’t tell what it was. But I saw Chibuike playing with the thing before it exploded. It is like he came to school with it. The thing chopped off his left hand. He has been taken to the Hospital, one of the students narrated.” When contacted, the State Police Public Relations Officer, DSP Loveth Odah, confirmed the incident but said she was yet to get official report from the DPO of Eke-Aba Police station, under whose jurisdiction the incident happened. “The DPO has gone there, but he has not reported to us. So, we are still waiting for him,’’ Odah said.